Rtractor — third-party code attribution
========================================

This file records the provenance of reference implementations wrapped or
ported into Rtractor, per the terms of their original licenses.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
src/dfa.cpp  (direct C++ port — wraps GPL-licensed reference code)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ported from dfa.c, distributed by PhysioNet.

Original copyright:
  Copyright (C) 2001-2005 Joe Mietus, C-K Peng, and George B. Moody

Original license:
  GNU General Public License, version 2, or (at your option) any later
  version. (This is why Rtractor as a whole is licensed GPL (>= 2).)

The R-level function dfa() in R/fractal.R reimplements the same
algorithm (box-size geometric series, per-box polynomial detrending via
normal equations, RMS fluctuation) in C++, validated to match the
original compiled binary's output exactly on synthetic test data.

